The Google Search Console API provides data about the performance of your site on Google Search engine with various methods to verify sites and view, add, or remove sitemaps, but it does not provide a direct way to access the &#39;Crawled - currently not indexed&#39; data upfront.

However, you can use the URL Inspection API endpoint to check the index status of a specific URL. Here is a sample Java code snippet using Google&#39;s client libraries to call the URL Inspection API:

```
import com.google.api.services.urlinspector.Urlinspector;
import com.google.api.services.urlinspector.model.UrlInspectionResult;

public class UrlInspectorSample {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        // Initialize the client
        Urlinspector urlinspector = new Urlinspector.Builder(
                GoogleNetHttpTransport.newTrustedTransport(),
                JacksonFactory.getDefaultInstance(),
                null)
                .setApplicationName(&quot;UrlInspectorSample&quot;)
                .build();

        // Specify the URL to inspect
        String urlToInspect = &quot;http://www.example.com&quot;;

        // Call the API
        UrlInspectionResult result = urlinspector.urlInspection().inspect(urlToInspect).execute();

        // Print the result
        System.out.println(&quot;URL: &quot; + urlToInspect);
        System.out.println(&quot;Index status: &quot; + result.getIndexStatusResult().getVerdict());
    }
}
```
*Disclaimer: untested and hastily written code above, provided as a starting point/sample idea only*

Please note that you need to replace &quot;http://www.example.com&quot; with the URL you want to inspect. This code will print the index status of the specified URL.

To get the list of &#39;Crawled - currently not indexed&#39; URLs, you would need to have a list of URLs to check, and then you could iterate over them and call the URL Inspection API for each one, and check if the index status is &#39;Crawled - currently not indexed&#39;. You&#39;ll still need to generate a list to iterate over and check. If you have a sitemap, you could use that to get the list of URLs.

Further, the API will not return the string &#39;Crawled - currently not indexed&#39;. You&#39;ll have to export the list manually, ping those URLs and compare the responses (I believe only within Verdict and/or IndexingState) to ascertain which values in the API meet your criteria.

