If you are using a custom layout for your menu, it doesn&#39;t call `onOptionsItemSelected()` by default. So you need to implement a click listener. You can follow [this tutorial][1] for more details.
```
    @Override
    public boolean onPrepareOptionsMenu(Menu menu) {
        final MenuItem menuItem = menu.findItem(R.id.navigation_refine);
        View rootView =  menuItem.getActionView();

        rootView.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                onOptionsItemSelected(menuItem);
            }
        });

        return super.onPrepareOptionsMenu(menu);
    }
```


